							This lesson puts equal emphasis on the history of the trans-Atlantic
							slave trade and on the craft of forming historical arguments.
							Students are asked to read a recent work from David Brion Davis,
							a leading historian of slavery, and to compare his arguments with
							evidence from the database.  This forms the foundation for a discussion
							of what kinds of claims are harder to defend than others and why some types
							of evidence are more convincing than others.
